-- Ten-Man Real Madrid Beats Sociedad 4-3 as Ronaldo Scores Twice
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-01-06T18:15:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-06/ten-man-real-madrid-beats-sociedad-4-3-as-ronaldo-scores-twice.html
Real  Madrid  recovered from goalkeeper
Antonio Adan’s sixth-minute red card to beat Real Sociedad 4-3
in Spain’s Primera Liga today.  Cristiano Ronaldo got two goals for Madrid after Karim Benzema and Sami Khedira also scored at the Santiago Bernabeu
stadium. Xabi Prieto got all the goals for Sociedad, who had
Daniel Estrada sent off in the 79th minute for a second yellow
card.  Madrid captain Iker Casillas, again left out by coach Jose Mourinho, came off the substitutes’ bench to replace Adan after
his dismissal for bringing down Carlos Vela.  Real Madrid, in third place, is 13 points behind leader
Barcelona, which hosts city rival Espanyol today. Second-placed
Atletico Madrid, which plays at Real Mallorca, is nine points
adrift of Barcelona.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at 
 celser@bloomberg.net . 